  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.10.14\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nMetrics (as with `--metrics`) should be enabled by the entry in the config file `[Metrics] Enabled = true`.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nMetrics are not enabled.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. Dump config for metrics.\r\n   ```\r\n   geth --metrics dumpconfig\r\n   ```\r\n   You will geth section as\r\n   ```\r\n   [Metrics]\r\n   Enabled = true\r\n   HTTP = \"127.0.0.1\"\r\n   Port = 6060\r\n   InfluxDBEndpoint = \"http://localhost:8086\"\r\n   InfluxDBDatabase = \"geth\"\r\n   InfluxDBUsername = \"test\"\r\n   InfluxDBPassword = \"test\"\r\n   InfluxDBTags = \"host=localhost\"\r\n   ```\r\n2. Try if metrics work at all.\r\n   ```\r\n   geth --metrics\r\n   INFO [01-02|11:28:29.998] Starting Geth on Ethereum mainnet... \r\n   INFO [01-02|11:28:29.998] Enabling metrics collection \r\n   ```\r\n3. Try with config file.\r\n   ```\r\n   geth --config metrics.toml\r\n   ```\r\n   The log \"Enabling metrics collection\" does not show up. The server at localhost:6060 does not work.\r\n",
